File: Lightbulb Pixabay JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will implement Stage 2 load-shedding from 6 am until 11 pm on Saturday. It warned load-shedding will also be implemented on Sunday as the system is severely constrained. The power utility explained a number of unforeseen breakdowns necessitated the power cuts. LOAD-SHEDDING: Schedules, info, and how it affects you Eskom said the weekend load shedding is necessary to replenish depleted generation reserves for the coming week. The utility is urging all South Africans to use electricity sparingly.